Real Madrid Wins to Open Six-Point Lead Over Barcelona in Spain’s La Liga

-- B y   C h r i s t o p h e r   E l s e r
-- 
2011-12-03T20:22:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-03/real-madrid-wins-to-open-six-point-lead-over-barcelona-in-spain-s-la-liga.html
Real Madrid beat Sporting Gijon 3-0
to open up a six-point lead over Barcelona at the top of Spanish
soccer’s La Liga.  Angel  Di Maria , Cristiano Ronaldo and Marcelo scored.
Barcelona plays Levante later today. Next week, Real and
Barcelona meet in Real’s Santiago Bernabeu stadium in the first
Clasico of the season.  Racing Santander defeated Villarreal 1-0 with a Christian
Stuani goal, lifting his club out of last place.  In Germany,  Bayern Munich  went to the top of the table
after getting two goals each from Franck Ribery and Arjen Robben
to win 4-2 at Werder Bremen. Dortmund lost ground after a 1-1
tie with Borussia Moenchengladbach.  Kaiserslautern tied Hertha Berlin 1-1, and Freiburg also
drew 1-1 with Hanover. Wolfsburg and Mainz tied 2-2, and
Dortmund tied 1-1. Stuttgart drew 2-2 with Cologne. Yesterday,
 Bayer Leverkusen  beat Hoffenheim 2-0.  In France, Montpellier won 4-0 against Lorient to take a
five-point lead in Ligue 1, and Lille moved into second with a a
3-2 win at Ajaccio. Brest and Saint-Etienne drew 2-2, Dijon tied
0-0 with Sochaux and Evian beat Valenciennes 2-1.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Christopher Elser at 
 celser@bloomberg.net  